  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Engineer - PUB Waterworks",
  "description": "<p><strong>Resident Engineer (Civil & Structural)</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead site supervision for all civil, structural, and building construction works.</p></li><li><p>Assist the Chief Resident Engineer and Construction Manager on site inspections, contract matters, defect identification, and rectification works.</p></li><li><p>Review and respond to contractors’ RFIs, technical submissions, method statements, and instrumentation readings; coordinate with other disciplines and liaise with the design team/QP.</p></li><li><p>Attend and lead site meetings with clients and contractors on technical and progress matters.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Civil & Structural Engineering, preferably recognised by the PE Board, Singapore.</p></li><li><p>At least 10 years of experience supervising civil and structural works, preferably in water/used water treatment projects.</p></li><li><p>Registered with IES as Resident Engineer (Civil).</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and leadership skills.</p></li></ul>",
